caption: Its construction dates from 1736. Inside, you can admire the stations of the cross in bas-relief, the baptismal font, the stained glass windows, the paintings including "the baptism of Christ" and a copy of the "Visitation" by Poussin and another of Prud'hon's "Christ on the Cross", funerary steles including that of Emile de Sommariva, lieutenant of hussars, son of the lord of Epinay and that of the Countess d’Houdetot, daughter of a former lord of Epinay. At the back of the church, on the square, a sculpture by Mauro Corda and the war memorial with the bronze statue from 1922 representing "Victory" by the sculptor Carlo Sarrabezolles and the Andro foundry. The current church was built in 1736 on the site of a church that had fallen into ruin. There is also the tomb of Louis-Denis Lalive de Bellegarde and his wife, Marie-Joséphine Prouveur, former lords of the place. The church has a large organ from 1893.
